cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SD 

This paper deals with sarcasm detection in social media, which is a common topic in the natural language processing (NLP) community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with social media users and their behavior, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of Bayesian methods and dense embeddings also suggests that the paper could be classified under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
